1. Setting up a Docker environment.
2. Creating a Cypress test file.
3. Integrating screenshot functionality.
4. Saving screenshots to a specified directory.

### Step 1: Setting Up a Docker Environment

First, you need to have Docker installed. Follow the installation guide for your operating system from the [official Docker website](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/).

### Step 2: Creating a Cypress Test File

Create a file named `test-cypress.js` for your Cypress tests.

```javascript
